ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is a lot of work, so take it only if you have the time to devote to it. If you can afford the time, however, it's a very fulfilling class where you will learn a ton.
I would recommend it with the stipulation that they must be prepared to do a lot of work as it is a very time intensive class. However, you do learn a tremendous amount throughout the class.
An interesting course, especially to gain hands on experience in attempting to grow/engineer a tissue.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This was an incredibly useful course, especially given this is the field I am in. I learned a ton and will use the knowledge extensively moving forward.
